upation with problems of origin. The present volume, going beyond identifying sources, analyses the socio-literary contexts and ideological foundations of seemingly similar contents and concepts in different periods; it examines the literary functions of borrowing and intertextual referencing, and calls upon the visual arts to illustrate the independent character of the epic tradition in Southeast Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Apr 2019) 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh1 aDing, Choo Ming, eeditor.1 avan der Molen, Willem, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2018z978311060677540uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/9789814786584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814786584.jpg  a978-3-11-060677-5  ISEAS eBook Package 2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG